<subSubSection id="C32BEEEAFFC6FF955FDDFDDAFB46FD1C" pageId="12" pageNumber="15" type="key">
<keyStep id="30C5A5C4FFC6FF955FDDFDDAFB46FED3" pageId="12" pageNumber="15">
<paragraph id="8B8EBD61FFC6FF955FDDFDDAFB46FE8A" blockId="12.[166,1226,221,646]" pageId="12" pageNumber="15">
<keyLead id="30C01E54FFC6FF955FDDFDDAFB46FE8A" pageId="12" pageNumber="15">1. Dorsal soft cuticle hypertrichous (with more than 30 pairs of setae); sternal shield with three pairs of lyrifissures. ........................................................................................................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8EBD61FFC6FF955FDDFC10FB46FED3" blockId="12.[166,1226,221,646]" pageId="12" pageNumber="15">
<keyLead id="30C01E54FFC6FF955FDDFC10FB46FED3" pageId="12" pageNumber="15">— Dorsal soft cuticle non hypertrichous (with less than 15 pairs of setae); sternal shield with two pairs of lyrifissures. ........................................................................................................................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30C5A5C4FFC6FF955FDDFC57FB46FE27" pageId="12" pageNumber="15">
<paragraph id="8B8EBD61FFC6FF955FDDFC57FB47FE19" blockId="12.[166,1226,221,646]" pageId="12" pageNumber="15">
<keyLead id="30C01E54FFC6FF955FDDFC57FB47FE19" pageId="12" pageNumber="15">
2. Peritrematal shields long, extending to level of coxae I; dorsal shield with 39 pairs of setae (Px2–3 present). ............................................................................................................................. 
